      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's... poetic I guess, but I don't think it's about the 'heartbeat of the universe.' It feels more clinical than that. Like, when the pulse speeds up, I feel this sudden wave of anxiety or just this weird urge to check my phone constantly. It's like the hum is actually broadcasting something that messes with your head. Dont you think it's possible for those frequencies to be manipulated?",
